sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shi Lei, W Ling , Nelson Chu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The fusion protein omp(46-159)streptavidin(WT) with a 6-histidine tail is linked after a pTet promoter. The fusion protein coding region does not contain any terminator. The omp domain directs the expression of the fusion protein on the surface membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pTet promoter, rbs are from the registry The fusion protein is self-designed

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nelson Chu, W Ling , Shi Lei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The chez is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement and is tagged by a 6-histidine tail. The pLac promoter can be repressed by LacI repressor protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The chez-histag coding region is self-designed The pLac promoter , rbs are from the registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shi Lei, W Ling , Nelson Chu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ssrB protein under pTet promoter. The ssrB protein can activate the prosseA promoter. The pTet promoter can be repressed by TetR repressor protein. The ssrB coding region does not contain any terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The ssrB coding region is self-designed The rbs and the pTet promoter are from the registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for part of the protein invisine. When fused with other protein, it can direct the protein to be expressed on the membrane

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K732002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Joshua Fass
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct contains a strong constitutive promoter (J23119) as well as an RBS (B0034) upstream of synCG-β (K732001), and should strongly express a synthetic version of the beta subunit of human chorionic gonadotropin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter and RBS will drive and enable efficient expression of the synthetic coding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Three BioBricks, one of which is from T7 bacteriophage, another of which is derived from a human gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of ''glgC''16 from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109 (see [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K118016 BBa_K118016]) with a ribosome binding site coupled to an upstream Lac promoter and ''lacZ''' as a method for testing expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K499596
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: luxC (acyl CoA reductase) with a strong promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Perry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: As per BBa_K499595, with a T7 promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We want lots of this, so we used a strong promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Plac-sam8
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of sam8, encoding tyrosine ammonia lyase (converts tyrosine to p-coumaric acid) from the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 44229, inserted downstream of a lac promoter with attached lacZ' minigene. The purpose of this was to ensure sam8 expression on induction with IPTG and also to provide a visually selectable tag when assembling the entire pathway; by always inserting a lacZ'-containing part into a non-lacZ'-containing part it is easy to select the correct clones on the basis that they form blue colonies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: sam8 is derived from Saccharothix espanaensis DSM 44229. The lac promoter and lacZ' minigene, encoding the N-terminal 76 amino acid residues of LacZ, are derived from Escherichia coli BS(DE3).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nelson Chu, W Ling , Shi Lei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consist of a chez downstream of a pLac promoter. The cheZ protein is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement. The pLac promoter can be repressed by LacI protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The chez coding region is self-designed The rbs and the pLac promomter are from the registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ninabGen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Christian Kurtzhals
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The Beta-carotene 15'15'-monooxygenase generator from the D. melanogaster ninaB gene, cleaves beta-carotene into two retinal molecules. Used together with BBa_274210 (beta-carotene generator) it should induce retinal biosynthesis in e. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: A constitutive sigma-70 promotor was chosen. Terminator is lacking on this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: [link:https://dgrc.cgb.indiana.edu/product/View?product=4630 Drosophila genomics ressource centre], Indiana University. Found via [link:http://www.flybase.org flybase], ID: [link:http://flybase.org/reports/FBcl0129473.html FBcl0129473]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yu bin, Jiang QinQin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of a fusion protein Lpp-rbs-protein under the pLac promoter. The Lpp is a signal peptide. The ompA domain of the fusion directs the protein to the surface membrane. The pLac promoter can be repressed by LacI protein. This part lacks a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pLac promoter, rbs sequence are obtained from the registry The fusion protein coding sequence is self-designed

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nelson Chu, W Ling , Shi Lei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: THe pTet promoter can be repressed by TetR repressor protein. The cI protein generated can repress plambda(R-O12)(K094002) promoter. This part lacks a terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pTet promoter and the rbs comes from the registry, The cI protein comes from lambda phage

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of glgC from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109 (see [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K118015 BBa_K118015]) with a ribosome binding site coupled to an upstream Lac promoter and ''lacZ''' as a method for testing expression.
